ReadOnly : False
Display Name : Enable Thunderbolt" Boot Support
Help String : When enabled, the following Thunderbolt" adapter features are enabled during Pre-boot:  Thunderbolt" adapter boot support, USB device on Thunderbolt" adapter support (including USB boot support). This allows Thunderbolt" adapter peripheral devices and USB devices connected to the Thunderbolt" adapter to be used during BIOS pre-boot. However, setting this to "Enabled" will override the Security Levels utilized within the operating system. When this setting is enabled, any Thunderbolt" adapter peripherals and USB devices connected to theThunderbolt" adapter port prior to booting the system can be used in pre-boot. As long as the device remains connected, it will continue to function within the operating system, regardless of the Security Level set in BIOS. 

