Display Name : Enable Intel AMT Capability
Help String : Disable Intel AMT Capability  = Intel Active Management Technology is disabled, MEBx will not be available
in pre-boot. Once disabled, Intel Active Management Technology can only be
enabled via BIOS interface. If the Intel AMT is already provisioned, AMT cannot be
disabled.(Unprovisioning AMT is required first to disable AMT)
Enable Intel AMT Capability  = Intel Active Management Technology is enabled, MEBx will be available
via F12 menu and customer can provision AMT. MEBx will not accessible if Device
Configuration Hotkey Access is disabled or BIOS admin password is not set. 
Restrict MEBx Access = Intel Active Management Technology is enabled, MEBx will not be available
in pre-boot and customer can provision AMT from OS.
Restrict Preboot Access = Intel Active Management Technology is enabled, MEBx and USB 
provisioning will not be available in pre-boot and customer can provision AMT from OS.

