Enumeration Attribute : 
Name : DeviceHotkeyAccess
ReadOnly : False
Display Name : Device Configuration Hotkey Access
Help String : This setting manages whether users can access device configuration screens via hotkeys during system startup. This setting prevents user access to Intel® RAID (CTRL+I), LSI RAID (CTRL+C), or Intel® Management Engine BIOS Extension (CTRL+P/F12).
Enable = User can access device configuration screens using hotkeys.
One Time Enable = User can access device configuration screens using hotkeys upon the next system startup only. After the next startup, this setting will revert to a disabled state.
Disable = User cannot access device configuration screens using hotkeys.
Enabling Device Configuration Hotkey Access allows users to access device configuration screen by pressing the hotkeys during system startup.
One-Time Enable allows access to device configuration screens via hotkeys only during the next system startup. After the next startup, this setting will revert to a disabled state.
Disabling Device Configuration Hotkey Access will prevent users from accessing Intel® RAID (CTRL+I), LSI RAID (CTRL+C), and Intel® Management Engine BIOS Extension (CTRL+P/F12).

Possible Values : Enabled OnetimeEnable Disabled 
Possible Values (Display Name) : Enabled, One Time Enable, Disabled
Default Values : Enabled 
Current Value : Enabled 

